abstract.gco:CharacterString: This data layer represents buildings for Sauk County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, "Sauk_Buildings_2018.gdb". [The creation of the subsequent building footprint data was executed to capture the existing ground conditions at a specific point in time using Stereo Imagery for the purpose of GIS analysis. GIS is a system of computer software, hardware, and data that allows a user to manipulate, analyze, and present information that is tied to a spatial location. Sauk contracted with the Sanborn Map Company to execute a collection of various buildings types that meet contract requirements.]

purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Building polygons for Sauk, Wisconsin. For 1"=100' or (1:1200) source scale mapping (6" GSD imagery): all structures with roofs having a area of 100 square feet or greater are captured from the stereo photography as a polygon. Buildings are delineated by tracing the eave line of the structure for dwellings, businesses, houses, house trailers, garages, barns, and accessory structures.]
